.TH "dwc2_gadget_get_chain_limit" 9 "dwc2_gadget_get_chain_limit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dwc2_gadget_get_chain_limit \- get the maximum data payload value of the DMA descriptor chain prepared for specific endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" dwc2_gadget_get_chain_limit
.BI "(struct dwc2_hsotg_ep *hs_ep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hs_ep" 12
The endpoint
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the maximum data that can be queued in one go on a given endpoint
depending on its descriptor chain capacity so that transfers that
are too long can be split.
